    <description>Nomads No More (NNM) is a free game system that includes two different games: Ungern&amp;rsquo;s Mongolia and Pasha&amp;rsquo;s Bokhara. Both games in the NNM system use the same core rules but use separate maps and pieces to cover concurrent conflicts that erupted on the eastern perimeter of Soviet Russia soon after the Russian Civil War &amp;ndash; the early 1920s. Ungern&amp;rsquo;s Mongolia simulates the invasion of Mongolia by fleeing Whites, their clash with the Chinese and subsequent pursuit by Reds. Pasha&amp;rsquo;s Bokhara covers the Basmachi uprising against Soviet rule around Bokhara - present day Kyrgyzstan, Tajikistan and Uzbekistan.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Published in Paper Wars #86 (Summer 2017 issue); publisher Compass Games.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
